DSA/Javascript Specific/Array Prototype.title: Array Prototype Last
DSA/Javascript Specific/Array Prototype.description: Write code that enhances all arrays such that you can call the array.last() method on any array and it will return the last element. If there are no elements in the array, it should return -1.

DSA/Javascript Specific/Compact Object.title: Compact Object
DSA/Javascript Specific/Compact Object.description: Given an object or array obj, return a compact object. A compact object is the same as the original object, except with keys containing falsy values removed. This operation applies to the object and any nested objects. Arrays are considered objects where the indices are keys. A value is considered falsy when Boolean(value) returns false.

DSA/Javascript Specific/Container with m.title: Container with most water
DSA/Javascript Specific/Container with m.description: You are given an integer array height of length n. There are n vertical lines drawn such that the two endpoints of the ith line are (i, 0) and (i, height[i]).

DSA/Javascript Specific/Counter.title: Counter
DSA/Javascript Specific/Counter.description: Given an integer n, return a counter function. This counter function initially returns n and then returns 1 more than the previous value every subsequent time it is called (n, n + 1, n + 2, etc).

DSA/Javascript Specific/Join Two Arrays.title: Join Two Arrays By Id
DSA/Javascript Specific/Join Two Arrays.description: Given two arrays arr1 and arr2, return a new array joinedArray. All the objects in each of the two inputs arrays will contain an id field that has an integer value. joinedArray is an array formed by merging arr1 and arr2 based on their id key. The length of joinedArray should be the length of unique values of id. The returned array should be sorted in ascending order based on the id key.
